# Privacy Policy for GeiDeLei

**Last updated:** 2026-07-14

GeiDeLei ("the app") is built to do one thing — listen to a word, translate it, and
speak it back — without collecting, storing, or selling any personal information
about you.

## What we don't do

- We don't collect, log, or store your voice, your translations, or any personal
  information.
- We don't require an account, sign-in, or profile of any kind.
- We don't use analytics, tracking, or advertising SDKs.
- We don't sell or share data with advertisers or data brokers.
- Nothing you say is saved anywhere — not on your device beyond the current
  session, and not on any server we control, because we don't operate one.

## What the app actually does with your voice

Speech recognition happens entirely on your device using Apple's built-in Speech
framework — the audio never leaves your phone for this step.

To translate the recognized word, the app sends that single word (not a recording,
not any other information) to one of the following third-party translation
services, depending on which one you've selected in the app's settings:

- MyMemory (api.mymemory.translated.net)
- LibreTranslate, via community-run instances (e.g. translate.fedilab.app)
- Google Translate's public translation endpoint (translate.googleapis.com)

These services receive only the text of the word being translated and the source/
target language codes — no name, no device identifier, no account, no location.
We don't control these third-party services and encourage you to review their own
privacy practices if you'd like more detail. This transmission happens only while
you're actively using the app to translate; nothing is sent in the background.

## Microphone and speech recognition permissions

The app asks for microphone and speech recognition access solely to hear the word
you want translated. These permissions are used only while the app is open and
actively listening, and you can revoke them at any time in Settings → GeiDeLei.

## Children's privacy

GeiDeLei does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including
children, because it does not collect information from anyone at all.

## Changes to this policy

If this policy ever changes — for example, if a future version of the app adds a
feature that involves data collection — this page will be updated and the "Last
updated" date above will reflect that.

